# TailwindCSS Styling

## Design Tokens
Custom theme tokens defined in `web/tailwind.config.js`:
- **`primary-*`** — sky blue scale (50–950), main brand color
- **`accent-*`** — fuchsia scale (50–950), accent/highlight color
- **Font:** `font-sans` = Outfit, `font-display` = Clash Display

Use these tokens for consistency. Avoid raw color values when a token exists.

## `cn()` Utility
Located in `web/src/utils/cn.ts` — standard `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` pattern.

```tsx
import { cn } from '@/utils/cn';

// ✅ Use cn() for conditional/variant classes
<button className={cn(
  'px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium',
  isActive ? 'bg-primary-600 text-white' : 'bg-gray-100 text-gray-600',
  className
)} />

// ❌ Avoid template literal ternaries for complex conditionals
<button className={`px-4 ${isActive ? 'bg-primary-600' : 'bg-gray-100'}`} />
```

## UI Primitive Pattern (`components/ui/`)
Variant/size lookup objects merged with `cn()`:

```tsx
const variants = {
  primary: 'bg-primary-600 text-white hover:bg-primary-700',
  secondary: 'bg-gray-100 text-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-200',
  ghost: 'hover:bg-gray-100 text-gray-600',
};

const sizes = {
  sm: 'px-3 py-1.5 text-sm',
  md: 'px-4 py-2 text-base',
  lg: 'px-6 py-3 text-lg',
};

export const Button: React.FC<ButtonProps> = ({ variant = 'primary', size = 'md', className, ...props }) => (
  <button className={cn(variants[variant], sizes[size], className)} {...props} />
);
```

## Page Layout
Standard page wrapper pattern:
```tsx
<div className="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-b from-amber-50/50 to-white">
  <div className="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    {/* content */}
  </div>
</div>
```

## Accessibility
UI primitives (`Button`, `Card`, shared `HobbyCard`) include:
- `aria-label`, `aria-hidden` on decorative icons
- `focus-visible:ring-*` focus indicators
- Maintain this in new components

## Do NOT
- Create new `.btn-*` or `.card` classes in `index.css` — use component-level Tailwind utilities
- Use colors outside the theme without good reason
- Skip `cn()` for conditional classes in reusable components
